example of using PowerShell to deploy updates via WSUS:

Approve Updates in WSUS:

powershell
Copy code
Import-Module UpdateServices
$wsus = Get-WsusServer -Name "YourWSUSServer" -Port 8530
$update = $wsus.GetUpdate("UpdateID")
$update.Approve("Install", $wsus.GetComputerTargetGroups() | Where-Object { $_.Name -eq "TargetGroupName" })
PowerShell Script to Trigger Update Installation on Clients:

powershell
Copy code
$servers = Get-Content -Path "servers.txt"
$scriptBlock = {
    Invoke-WUJob -ComputerName $env:COMPUTERNAME -Script {
        Invoke-WUInstall -AcceptAll -IgnoreReboot
    } -Confirm:$false
}
foreach ($server in $servers) {
    Invoke-Command -ComputerName $server -ScriptBlock $scriptBlock
}
